This paper discusses the software architecture for general purpose robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of low-level skills such as manipulation and perception, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed architecture involves a reactive module, which can be seen as a form of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the architecture on a domestic service robot platform, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
